nodes.body:
I think either of "binary coproducts + initial object" and "binary products + terminal object" suffices to obtain a CommMonoid structure on the skeleton. The conditions used in this PR ("binary biproucts + zero object") are a combination of both, so should be derivable from either.

It would be reasonable to associate an additive monoid structure to "binary coproducts + initial object" and a multiplicative monoid structure to "binary products + terminal object".

For the latter there is [CategoryTheory.MonoidalOfChosenFiniteProducts.instMonoidalCategoryMonoidalOfChosenFiniteProductsSynonymInstCategoryMonoidalOfChosenFiniteProductsSynonym](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/OfChosenFiniteProducts/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.MonoidalOfChosenFiniteProducts.instMonoidalCategoryMonoidalOfChosenFiniteProductsSynonymInstCategoryMonoidalOfChosenFiniteProductsSynonym)
